==English==

===Noun===
'''epoche'''

# Moment of theoretical suspension of all action.
# Moment of theoretical suspension of disbelief.

===Origin===
This term was introduced by Husserel and other phenomenologists, although it seems to also be present in Aristotilian philosophy as well (as the concept did originate with Aristotle) and is a corruption of the word "epoch."